===================================================================
Sorter Benchmark, by David J. Pearce, July 2011
===================================================================

This benchmark is a very straightforward implementation of a merge
sort.  The Java version uses a fairly straightforward implementation
of an in-place merge sort, using a temporary array and an int[] for
storing the data.

===================================================================
Inputs
===================================================================

small.in  : 1000 randomly shuffled items in range 0-999

medium.in : 10000 randomly shuffled items in range 0-9999

large.in  : 100000 randomly shuffled items in range 0-99999

See Gen.java for code which generated the input files.

